{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Rom|12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":12,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":1,"text":"Therefore, brothers and sisters, in view of the mercies of God, I urge you to present your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and pleasing to God; this is your true worship.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":2,"text":"Do not be conformed to this age, but be transformed by the renewing of your mind, so that you may discern what is the good, pleasing, and perfect will of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":3,"text":"For by the grace given to me, I tell everyone among you not to think of himself more highly than he should think. Instead, think sensibly, as God has distributed a measure of faith to each one.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":4,"text":"Now as we have many parts in one body, and all the parts do not have the same function,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":5,"text":"in the same way we who are many are one body in Christ and individually members of one another.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":6,"text":"According to the grace given to us, we have different gifts: If prophecy, use it according to the proportion of one’s faith;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":7,"text":"if service, use it in service; if teaching, in teaching;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":8,"text":"if exhorting, in exhortation; giving, with generosity; leading, with diligence; showing mercy, with cheerfulness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":9,"text":"Let love be without hypocrisy. Detest evil; cling to what is good.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":10,"text":"Love one another deeply as brothers and sisters. Take the lead in honoring one another.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":11,"text":"Do not lack diligence in zeal; be fervent in the Spirit; serve the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":12,"text":"Rejoice in hope; be patient in affliction; be persistent in prayer.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":13,"text":"Share with the saints in their needs; pursue hospitality.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":14,"text":"Bless those who persecute you; bless and do not curse.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":15,"text":"Rejoice with those who rejoice; weep with those who weep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":16,"text":"Live in harmony with one another. Do not be proud; instead, associate with the humble. Do not be wise in your own estimation.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":17,"text":"Do not repay anyone evil for evil. Give careful thought to do what is honorable in everyone’s eyes.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":18,"text":"If possible, as far as it depends on you, live at peace with everyone.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":19,"text":"Friends, do not avenge yourselves; instead, leave room for God’s wrath, because it is written, Vengeance belongs to me; I will repay, says the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":20,"text":"But","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:12:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":12,"verse":21,"text":"Do not be conquered by evil, but conquer evil with good.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":12,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,9,21],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"A Living Sacri